  "text": "All patients underwent a detailed neurobehavioral assessment within the 4 weeks before their MRI scan, involving a neurological examination, psychosocial interview, and neuropsychological testing, and were designated as having no, mild, or moderate (coded as 0, 1, and 2 respectively) neuropsychological impairment based on a factor analysis of a broad inventory of motor and cognitive tests performed by a neuropsychologist [CITATION_1] .",
